article.headline: Wildcats' Wheeler slams the door on Huskies
article.linkText: Arizona's Wheeler slams the door on Washington
article.story:
TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) -- Dee-Dee Wheeler scored 25 points, and hit a key 3 to halt Washington's momentum and lead Arizona to a 79-66 victory Thursday night.

The Huskies (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP, 17-4 overall, 9-3 Pac-10) closed a 17-point second-half deficit to 51-45 with 13:01 left following a jumper by Loree Payne. But Arizona (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today, 15-6, 8-4) responded with a 3-pointer by Wheeler, a layup by Shawntinice Polk and a baseline jumper by Robin Roberson
for a 58-45 edge.

   Giuliana Mendiola led Washington with 22 points, and Payne added
21.

Arizona went ahead 66-53 by getting the ball inside on a pair of
drives by Wheeler and layups by CoCoa Sanford and Krista Warren
with just over eight minutes remaining to put the game away.

Polk and Warren added with 14 points apiece for Arizona, and
Aimee Grzyb scored 11.

   Washington fell behind 45-30 at halftime. The Huskies' troubles came early as Arizona was hot from the perimeter. The Wildcats' Grzyb made two of Arizona's four 3-pointers in a 15-2 run that gave it a 24-10 lead with 13:50 left.
